      <h1>Understanding Anxiety: A Complete GAD-7 Score Guide</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">Everyone experiences anxiety. It is a normal, even useful, emotional response that alerts you to potential threats and motivates you to prepare for challenges. But for tens of millions of people worldwide, anxiety stops being a helpful signal and becomes a chronic, overwhelming presence that disrupts daily life, relationships, and well-being. The GAD-7 is one of the most widely used tools in healthcare for measuring the severity of anxiety symptoms, and understanding how it works can help you make sense of what you are experiencing and decide when to seek professional support. This guide explains what anxiety is, how the GAD-7 screening works, what your score means, and what evidence-based treatments are available.</p>
    </header>

    <AdUnit slot="blog-top" format="horizontal" />

